-- The spawner creates 6 new cells. The program GROWS from 4 cells
-- (problem, analyze-problem, cell-template, integrate-results + meta)
-- to 10 cells. This is the bootstrap in action.

вҠўвҠў spawn-domain-cells
  given analyze-problemвҶ’needed-cells вүЎ [... 6 cell specs ...]
  given В§cell-template
  yield В§domain-cells[]

-- eval-one: spawner instantiates 6 cells from cell-template.
-- Each cell is wired per the needed-cells specification.

-- SPAWNED: research-ramen (root cell, no dependencies)

вҠў research-ramen
  given task-description вүЎ "Find the best ramen restaurants in Tokyo, covering different styles (tonkotsu, shoyu, miso, tsukemen) and neighborhoods."
  given dependencies вүЎ []
  yield result

  вҲҙ Research top ramen restaurants in Tokyo. Cover:
    - Different ramen styles: tonkotsu (pork bone), shoyu (soy sauce), miso, shio (salt), tsukemen (dipping)
    - Different neighborhoods: Shinjuku, Shibuya, Ikebukuro, Roppongi, Asakusa
    - Include both famous chains and hidden gems
    - Note approximate price range and any queueing expectations

  вҠЁ result includes at least 6 specific restaurants with names and neighborhoods
  вҠЁ result covers at least 3 different ramen styles

-- SPAWNED: research-architecture (root cell, no dependencies)

вҠў research-architecture
  given task-description вүЎ "Identify notable architectural landmarks in Tokyo вҖ” traditional temples, modern skyscrapers, famous buildings by renowned architects (Ando, Kuma, Tange)."
  given dependencies вүЎ []
  yield result

  вҲҙ Research architecturally significant buildings and sites in Tokyo. Cover:
    - Traditional: temples, shrines, gardens with notable architecture
    - Modern: skyscrapers, museums, cultural centers by famous architects
    - Architects: Tadao Ando, Kengo Kuma, Kenzo Tange, SANAA, Toyo Ito
    - Include opening hours and any admission fees

  вҠЁ result includes at least 8 specific sites with architect attribution where applicable
  вҠЁ result covers both traditional and modern architecture

-- SPAWNED: research-logistics (root cell, no dependencies)

вҠў research-logistics
  given task-description вүЎ "Gather practical info: Tokyo transit system (Suica card, JR lines, Metro), typical costs, neighborhood geography, weekend timing considerations."
  given dependencies вүЎ []
  yield result

  вҲҙ Research practical logistics for a Tokyo weekend trip:
    - Transit: Suica/Pasmo IC cards, JR Yamanote line, Tokyo Metro, cost per ride
    - Neighborhoods: relative locations, walking distances, key stations
    - Weekend specifics: which attractions are less crowded on weekends, typical shop hours
    - Budget: typical meal costs, transit day costs, admission fees

  вҠЁ result includes transit system overview with specific lines and costs
  вҠЁ result includes neighborhood geography useful for route planning

-- SPAWNED: plan-day-saturday

вҠў plan-day-saturday
  given research-ramenвҶ’result
  given research-architectureвҶ’result
  given research-logisticsвҶ’result
  yield result

  вҲҙ Build a Saturday itinerary combining ramen and architecture:
    - Morning: start with an architectural site that opens early
    - Lunch: a top ramen spot nearby
    - Afternoon: 2-3 more architectural sites in a walkable cluster
    - Dinner: another ramen restaurant, different style from lunch
    - Include specific transit directions between stops
    - Focus on one or two neighborhoods to minimize travel time

  вҠЁ result is a time-sequenced itinerary (morning вҶ’ evening)
  вҠЁ result includes at least 2 ramen meals and 3 architectural sites
  вҠЁ result includes transit directions between each stop

-- SPAWNED: plan-day-sunday

вҠў plan-day-sunday
  given research-ramenвҶ’result
  given research-architectureвҶ’result
  given research-logisticsвҶ’result
  given plan-day-saturdayвҶ’result
  yield result

  вҲҙ Build a Sunday itinerary that complements Saturday:
    - Choose DIFFERENT neighborhoods than Saturday
    - Cover ramen styles not yet tried
    - Visit architectural sites not yet seen
    - Account for Sunday-specific hours (some shrines busier, some shops closed)
    - Include a leisurely breakfast spot or morning activity
    - End at a reasonable time for departure

  вҠЁ result does not duplicate any Saturday venues
  вҠЁ result covers different neighborhoods than Saturday
  вҠЁ result includes at least 1 ramen meal and 2 architectural sites

-- SPAWNED: synthesize-itinerary

вҠў synthesize-itinerary
  given plan-day-saturdayвҶ’result
  given plan-day-sundayвҶ’result
  given research-logisticsвҶ’result
  yield result

  вҲҙ Combine Saturday and Sunday into a polished weekend itinerary:
    - Full schedule with times for both days
    - Total budget estimate
    - Packing/preparation tips
    - Alternative options if weather is bad or a spot is closed
    - A "best of" summary for someone short on time

  вҠЁ result is a complete, ready-to-use weekend itinerary
  вҠЁ result includes budget estimate
  вҠЁ result includes contingency alternatives

