1. Fuunji (Shinjuku) вҖ” TSUKEMEN. Legendary dipping noodles. Rich fish + pork broth. ВҘ1,000. Expect 20-30min queue.
2. Ichiran (Shibuya/Shinjuku/multiple) вҖ” TONKOTSU. Solo booth dining, customizable richness/noodle firmness. ВҘ980. Open 24hrs.
3. Afuri (Ebisu/Roppongi) вҖ” SHIO (yuzu salt). Light, citrusy broth. Modern interior. ВҘ1,100. Less queue than others.
4. Rokurinsha (Tokyo Station) вҖ” TSUKEMEN. Thick, chewy noodles in concentrated broth. ВҘ1,050. Ramen Street underground.
5. Menya Musashi (Shinjuku) вҖ” TONKOTSU SHOYU blend. Dual-soup style. ВҘ950. Near west exit.
6. Soranoiro (Tokyo Station) вҖ” VEGAN option available. Creative modern ramen. ВҘ1,200. Ramen Street.
7. Fuji Ramen (Asakusa) вҖ” SHOYU. Old-school Tokyo-style. Simple, clean flavors. ВҘ850. No queue on weekends.
8. Tsuta (Sugamo) вҖ” SHOYU. First Michelin-starred ramen. Truffle oil accent. ВҘ1,500. Reservation system.

Price range: ВҘ850-1,500 per bowl (~$6-10 USD). Most shops are counter-only, 10-20 seats."

