MODERN:
1. 21_21 Design Sight (Roppongi) вҖ” Tadao Ando. Sunken concrete gallery. ВҘ1,200. Closed Tues.
2. Nezu Museum (Omotesando) вҖ” Kengo Kuma. Bamboo faГ§ade, stunning garden. ВҘ1,300. Closed Mon.
3. National Art Center Tokyo (Roppongi) вҖ” Kisho Kurokawa. Undulating glass curtain wall. Free entry (exhibitions vary). Closed Tues.
4. Tokyo International Forum (Yurakucho) вҖ” Rafael ViГұoly. Ship-hull glass atrium. Free to enter.
5. Prada Aoyama (Omotesando) вҖ” Herzog & de Meuron. Diamond-grid glass faГ§ade. Free (retail).
6. Tokyo Skytree (Sumida) вҖ” Nikken Sekkei. 634m, neo-futuristic. ВҘ2,100-3,100. Open daily.
7. Nakagin Capsule Tower site (Ginza) вҖ” Kisho Kurokawa (demolished 2022, memorial plaque). Free.
8. teamLab Borderless (Azabudai Hills) вҖ” Digital art in Mori Building. ВҘ3,800. Open daily.

TRADITIONAL:
9. Senso-ji (Asakusa) вҖ” Tokyo's oldest temple, 7th century. Thunder Gate (Kaminarimon). Free. Opens 6am.
10. Meiji Jingu (Harajuku) вҖ” Shinto shrine in forest. Cypress wood torii gate. Free. Opens at sunrise.
11. Tokyo National Museum (Ueno) вҖ” Taniguchi Yoshiro main building, Imperial Crown style. ВҘ1,000. Closed Mon.
12. Nezu Shrine (Yanaka) вҖ” 1706, vermillion torii tunnel. Free. Quiet alternative to tourist shrines.

NEIGHBORHOODS FOR ARCHITECTURE WALKS:
- Omotesando: 'Champs-ГүlysГ©es of Tokyo' вҖ” Ando, Kuma, SANAA, Ito all have buildings on one street
- Roppongi: Art Triangle (National Art Center, Mori Art Museum, Suntory Museum)
- Asakusa/Sumida: Traditional + Skytree contrast"

