вҠў research-logistics
  given task-description вүЎ "Gather practical info: Tokyo transit system..."
  given dependencies вүЎ []
  yield result

-- LLM evaluation:

  yield result вүЎ "Tokyo Weekend Logistics:

TRANSIT:
- Get a Suica or Pasmo IC card at any station (ВҘ500 deposit + charge). Tap on/off everywhere.
- JR Yamanote Line: circular loop connecting Shinjuku, Shibuya, Harajuku, Tokyo, Ueno, Ikebukuro. ВҘ150-200 per ride.
- Tokyo Metro: 13 lines covering inner city. ВҘ170-320 per ride. 24-hour weekend pass: ВҘ600.
- JR + Metro day pass combo: not available. Use IC card вҖ” simpler.
- Google Maps works perfectly for Tokyo transit. Real-time, accurate.
- Last trains: ~midnight. First trains: ~5am.

NEIGHBORHOOD GEOGRAPHY (walking clusters):
- Roppongi вҶ” Omotesando: 1 stop (Chiyoda line) or 25min walk through Aoyama
- Asakusa вҶ’ Sumida/Skytree: 15min walk across river
- Harajuku вҶ” Omotesando: 5min walk (same area)
- Shinjuku вҶ” Shibuya: 2 stops (JR Yamanote) or 30min walk
- Ueno вҶ” Yanaka: 10min walk

WEEKEND SPECIFICS:
- Temples: busy Sat-Sun mornings. Go early (before 9am) or late afternoon.
- Ramen shops: peak 11:30-13:00. Go at 11:00 or after 14:00 to skip queues.
- Museums: closed Mon/Tues (varies). All open weekends.
- Shopping streets (Omotesando, Ginza): bustling but enjoyable.

BUDGET (per person, per day):
- Transit: ВҘ1,000-1,500
- Ramen lunch: ВҘ1,000
- Ramen dinner: ВҘ1,000
- Museum/attraction: ВҘ1,000-3,000
- Snacks/drinks: ВҘ500-1,000
- Daily total: ВҘ4,500-7,500 (~$30-50 USD)
- Weekend total: ВҘ9,000-15,000 (~$60-100 USD, excluding hotel)"

