8:00  Senso-ji temple (Asakusa) вҖ” Arrive at opening to see Thunder Gate
      and Nakamise shopping street before crowds. Tokyo's oldest temple.
      Photograph the five-story pagoda. (Free, Asakusa station Ginza line)

9:30  Walk to Tokyo Skytree (15min across Sumida River) вҖ” The 634m tower
      contrasts dramatically with old Asakusa. View from base is free.
      Observation deck: ВҘ2,100. Go early = no queue.

11:00 RAMEN LUNCH: Fuji Ramen (Asakusa, walk back 10min)
      Old-school Tokyo shoyu ramen. ВҘ850. No queue on weekends.
      Completely different style from yesterday's yuzu shio and tonkotsu.

12:00 Take Ginza line from Asakusa to Ueno (5min, 3 stops).

12:15 Tokyo National Museum (Ueno) вҖ” Imperial Crown architecture by
      Taniguchi. Japan's largest museum. Focus on the main building's
      architecture + Gallery of Horyuji Treasures (Taniguchi Yoshio,
      glass-and-water design). ВҘ1,000. Allow 2hrs.

14:30 Walk from Ueno to Yanaka (10min) вҖ” Through Ueno Park, past the
      old-Tokyo neighborhood. Wooden houses, narrow lanes, temple cats.
      Visit Nezu Shrine вҖ” 1706 vermillion torii tunnel, peaceful escape.
      (Free)

16:00 OPTIONAL: Tsuta ramen (Sugamo, 2 stops JR from Nishi-Nippori)
      Michelin-starred shoyu ramen with truffle. ВҘ1,500. If reservation
      available, don't miss it. If not, continue walking Yanaka.

17:00 Return to base. Ginza line or JR Yamanote back.

Transit: Ginza line (Asakusa вҶ” Ueno), JR Yamanote (Ueno area вҶ’ return).
Neighborhoods: Asakusa/Sumida cluster + Ueno/Yanaka cluster. All walkable within clusters.
Budget: ВҘ2,100 + ВҘ850 + ВҘ1,000 + ВҘ1,500 (optional) + ~ВҘ600 transit = ~ВҘ4,550-6,050"

