-- LLM evaluation:

  yield final-plan вүЎ "YOUR TOKYO WEEKEND: RAMEN Г— ARCHITECTURE

в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғ SATURDAY: Modern Tokyo в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғ

Morning вҖ” Harajuku & Omotesando
  08:30  Meiji Jingu вҖ” Tokyo's most serene shrine. Walk the gravel path
         through 100-year-old forest. The shrine itself: clean cypress lines,
         copper roof gone green. Free. JR Harajuku station, south exit.

  10:00  Omotesando Architecture Boulevard вҖ” Every major architect competed
         here. Walk south to north:
         вҖў Prada (Herzog & de Meuron) вҖ” diamond glass crystal
         вҖў Tod's (Toyo Ito) вҖ” tree-branch concrete lattice
         вҖў Dior (SANAA) вҖ” translucent organic curves
         All free to enter. Allow 60min for photos and browsing.

Lunch
  11:00  рҹҚң AFURI, Ebisu вҖ” Yuzu shio (salt + citrus) ramen. Light, fragrant,
         modern. Get the limited yuzu-tsukemen if available. ВҘ1,100.
         Hibiya line from Omotesando to Ebisu, 2 stops.

Afternoon вҖ” Roppongi Art Triangle
  12:30  21_21 Design Sight (Tadao Ando) вҖ” Sunken concrete gallery in
         Midtown garden. Ando's signature: raw concrete, light shafts.
         ВҘ1,200. Allow 60min.

  14:00  National Art Center Tokyo (Kisho Kurokawa) вҖ” The glass wave.
         16,000mВІ of undulating curtain wall. The cafГ© inside sits on
         inverted concrete cones. Free entry. 5min walk from 21_21.

  16:00  teamLab Borderless at Azabudai Hills вҖ” Digital art immersion
         inside Mori Building tower. Book tickets 2+ days ahead. ВҘ3,800.
         Allow 90-120min. 10min walk from Art Center.

Dinner
  18:30  рҹҚң ICHIRAN, Roppongi вҖ” The tonkotsu ritual. Solo booth, paper
         order form: richness, garlic, spice, noodle firmness. Classic
         Hakata-style pork bone broth. ВҘ980. Open 24hrs.

  рҹҡҮ Transit: Harajuku вҶ’ walk вҶ’ Omotesando вҶ’ Hibiya line вҶ’ Ebisu вҶ’ walk вҶ’ Roppongi
  рҹ’ҙ Budget: ~ВҘ8,900 (ramen ВҘ2,080 + attractions ВҘ6,200 + transit ВҘ600)

в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғ SUNDAY: Traditional Tokyo в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғ

Morning вҖ” Asakusa & Sumida
  08:00  Senso-ji вҖ” Tokyo's oldest temple (628 AD). Through the Thunder
         Gate (Kaminarimon), down Nakamise-dori, past the five-story pagoda.
         Arrive early вҖ” by 10am it's packed. Free. Ginza line to Asakusa.

  09:30  Tokyo Skytree вҖ” Walk 15min across Sumida River for the approach.
         The 634m tower is neo-futuristic steel lattice, designed after
         traditional Japanese 'sori' curves. Observation deck ВҘ2,100.
         Morning = shortest queue.

Lunch
  11:00  рҹҚң FUJI RAMEN, Asakusa вҖ” Old-school Tokyo shoyu. Clear soy broth,
         thin noodles, chashu, nori. What ramen was before it got famous.
         ВҘ850. Walk back from Skytree, 10min.

Afternoon вҖ” Ueno & Yanaka
  12:15  Tokyo National Museum, Ueno вҖ” Imperial Crown architecture (1937,
         Taniguchi Yoshiro). Inside: Gallery of Horyuji Treasures by his
         son (Taniguchi Yoshio) вҖ” glass-and-water minimalism. ВҘ1,000.
         Ginza line Asakusa вҶ’ Ueno, 5min. Allow 2hrs.

  14:30  Yanaka neighborhood walk вҖ” 10min walk from Ueno through old Tokyo.
         Wooden houses, narrow lanes, cat statues. Then Nezu Shrine (1706):
         a tunnel of vermillion torii gates in total silence. Free.

Late Afternoon (optional)
  16:00  рҹҚң TSUTA, Sugamo вҖ” First Michelin-starred ramen. Shoyu base with
         Italian truffle oil and sun-dried tomato. ВҘ1,500. Reservations
         via ticket machine. JR from Nishi-Nippori, 2 stops.

  рҹҡҮ Transit: Asakusa вҶ’ walk вҶ’ Skytree вҶ’ walk вҶ’ Asakusa вҶ’ Ginza line вҶ’ Ueno вҶ’ walk вҶ’ Yanaka вҶ’ JR
  рҹ’ҙ Budget: ~ВҘ5,450-6,950 (ramen ВҘ850-2,350 + attractions ВҘ3,100 + transit ВҘ700)

в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғ PRACTICAL NOTES в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғ

  рҹҺ« Transit: Buy Suica IC card at any JR station. ВҘ500 deposit + top up.
     Tap on/off for all JR, Metro, and buses. Google Maps for navigation.

  рҹ’ҙ Total weekend budget: ~ВҘ14,000-16,000 (~$95-110 USD)
     Excludes: hotel, flights, shopping

  вҳ” Rain plan: Swap outdoor walks for Mori Art Museum (ВҘ2,000, Roppongi Hills),
     Ginza underground shopping, or extra time at teamLab / National Museum.

  рҹҚң Ramen styles covered:
     вҖў Yuzu shio (Afuri) вҖ” light, citrus
     вҖў Tonkotsu (Ichiran) вҖ” rich, pork
     вҖў Shoyu (Fuji) вҖ” classic, clean
     вҖў Truffle shoyu (Tsuta) вҖ” Michelin, fancy

  рҹҸӣпёҸ Architecture covered:
     Traditional вҖ” Meiji Jingu, Senso-ji, Nezu Shrine
     Modern вҖ” Ando, Kurokawa, Herzog & de Meuron, Ito, SANAA, teamLab
     Monumental вҖ” Tokyo Skytree, Tokyo National Museum"

