вҠў= obs-bootstrap-from-zero
  yield observation вүЎ "The bootstrapper started with exactly 4 structural cells (problem, analyze-problem, cell-template, spawn-domain-cells) and zero domain knowledge. After frame 2, the program had 10 cells вҖ” 6 spawned by the meta-cell. The domain structure emerged entirely from LLM reasoning about the problem statement. This is Cell's bootstrap sequence: the spec defines the mechanism, the LLM provides the domain intelligence."

вҠў= obs-spawner-as-strategy
  yield observation вүЎ "вҠўвҠў spawn-domain-cells is not a parallelism optimization вҖ” it IS the program. Without it, there are no domain cells at all. The spawner transforms a meta-level description (needed-cells[]) into executable cells. This is eval/apply: analyze-problem is eval (what cells?), spawn-domain-cells is apply (create them)."

вҠў= obs-evolution-as-completeness
  yield observation вүЎ "вҠўвҲҳ evolve converged in one iteration because the initial cell decomposition scored 8/10 on completeness. The evolution loop's convergence criterion (needs-more-cells = false) tests structural adequacy, not output quality. Quality is handled by the oracle assertions on each individual cell. This separation is clean: вҠўвҲҳ grows the program, вҠЁ guards each cell."

вҠў= obs-meta-level-separation
  yield observation вүЎ "The meta-cell (analyze-problem) reasons about WHAT cells to create. The domain cells (research-ramen, plan-day-saturday, etc.) reason WITHIN their domains. Neither crosses the boundary. analyze-problem never writes ramen reviews. research-ramen doesn't know it was bootstrapped. This is the Liskov principle for Cell: meta-level and object-level are substitution-independent."

вҠў= obs-parallel-research-phase
  yield observation вүЎ "Frames 3-5 (research-ramen, research-architecture, research-logistics) were all in the ready set simultaneously after frame 2. Confluence guarantees any execution order gives the same result. In a parallel runtime, all three would execute simultaneously вҖ” the bootstrap naturally discovered parallelizable structure from the problem."

вҠў= obs-program-growth-trajectory
  yield observation вүЎ "Cell count trajectory: frame 0: 4 structural cells вҶ’ frame 2: 10 cells (6 spawned) вҶ’ frame 11: 10 cells (gap spawner added 0). The program could have grown to 15+ cells if completeness scored below 7. The trajectory is monotonic (cells only added) and oracle-gated (gaps must be specific). Growth terminates when the meta-cell judges sufficiency."

